{"link_name": "DB2 Basic Monitoring", "type": "Template", "OS": "", "vendor": "Others", "minZabbVer": "4.0.x", "link_desc": "<p>Here is my version of DB2 monitoring using Userparameters. It uses DB2 monitoring tools, and get values from it.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You may need to grant some rights, to zabbix user, like SYSIBMADM in order to execute monitoring requests.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You also need to enable DB2 monitoring tools, since userparameters use this feature. To do so : </p>\n<p>db2 update dbm cfg using DFT_MON_TABLE on</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\">db2 update dbm cfg using</span><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\"> </span>dft_mon_bufpool<span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\">on</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\">db2 update dbm cfg using</span><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\"> </span>dft_mon_lock<span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12.16px;\">on</span></p>", "features": "Database Monitor", "address": "", "city": "", "state": "", "country": "", "postcode": "", "telephone": "", "fax": "", "email": "", "website": "https://github.com/Fdvxcbd/DB2-Zbx", "price": 0, "link_hits": 3709, "link_votes": null, "link_rating": 0, "link_featured": null, "link_created": "2019-07-22 14:09:34", "link_modified": "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "link_visited": 1240, "publish_up": "2019-07-22 14:09:34", "publish_down": "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "metakey": "", "metadesc": "", "1.8": "", "2.0": "", "2.2": "", "2.4": "", "3.0": "", "3.2": "", "3.4": "", "4.0": "", "4.2": "", "4.4": "", "5.0": "", "5.2": "", "tags": "UserParameter, Template, DB2", "author": "", "user_id": 10329, "link_id": 1730, "cat_id": "152", "internal_notes": "", "lat": 0, "lng": 0, "zoom": ""}